---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import LegalArticle from "../components/LegalArticle.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Moss"
  description="Privacy policy for the Moss travel companion app."
  bodyClass="legal-page"
>
  <LegalArticle title="Privacy Policy" updated="19 July 2026">
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy explains how Moss ("the app", "we", "us") collects,
      uses, and protects your information when you use the Moss iOS app and
      website. By using Moss, you agree to the practices described below.
    </p>

    <h2>Information we collect</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Account information.</strong> When you create an account we store
        your email address and, optionally, profile details such as your display name.
        Authentication is handled by Supabase and may use email, Sign in with Apple,
        or Google Sign-In. If you choose Apple or Google, that provider processes
        the sign-in request and sends Supabase authentication data that may include
        a provider account identifier, email address, and profile details you
        authorize it to share.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Your travel content.</strong> Trips, destinations, itinerary items,
        places, notes, dates, categories, and related details you add are stored so
        they can sync across your devices.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Device tokens.</strong> If you enable push notifications we store
        an Apple Push Notification service token so we can send trip reminders and
        related app notifications.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Subscription information.</strong> If you subscribe to Supporter Monthly,
        Apple handles payment. We store subscription entitlement status and transaction
        identifiers needed to unlock paid features and keep access in sync.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How we use your information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        To provide the app's core features: planning trips, saving itinerary
        details, organizing places, syncing data, and sending reminders you opt
        into.
      </li>
      <li>
        To manage account access, password reset flows, sign-in providers,
        subscription entitlement, and account deletion requests.
      </li>
      <li>To maintain, secure, debug, and improve the service.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-party website resources</h2>
    <p>
      The Moss website loads typefaces from Google Fonts. When your browser
      requests those files, it connects directly to Google, which may receive
      technical request information such as your IP address and browser details.
      Google's handling of that information is governed by its own privacy
      policy.
    </p>

    <h2>How your information is shared</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell your personal information. Information is shared only with
      service providers needed to operate Moss, including Supabase for
      authentication and app data storage; Apple and Google for sign-in when
      selected; Apple for purchases and notifications; and Google Fonts for
      website typefaces. We may also disclose information when required by law.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain your information for as long as your account is active. You can
      delete your account from within the app settings screen. When you delete
      your account, your associated account data is removed from our systems.
    </p>

    <h2>Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use reasonable safeguards to protect your information, including
      encrypted connections, Supabase row-level security, and access controls.
      No method of transmission or storage is completely secure.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal
      information. To delete your account or make a request, use the in-app
      account deletion flow or contact us using the details below.
    </p>

    <h2>Children's privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Moss is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect
      personal information from children under 13.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will
      revise the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact us</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, contact us at <a
        href="mailto:support@getmoss.app">support@getmoss.app</a
      >.
    </p>
  </LegalArticle>
</BaseLayout>
